description:
&lt;p&gt;Theatre Practitioner ODP – Anaesthetics &amp; Recovery (RGN/ ODP)  - Cheltenham – Full Time (However Part Time can be considered)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work for a company that will truly invest in your career? Do you want to work in an environment where you have the time to dedicate time &amp; care to your patients? Do you want to work for the UKs not for profit healthcare provider? If so, Nuffield Health is looking for a Theatre Practitioner at our Nuffield Health Cheltenham Hospital. Get in touch or apply today! &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With drive, passion and high standards, you might join us from the NHS or a private setting. Either way, you will discover unrivalled scope to work autonomously, making full use of your skills and knowledge and adding value.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not only do we invest in your career through training and CPD, there’s free parking onsite, and you’ll be supported by an experienced and close knit team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Theatre Practitioner Nurse / ODP – Anaesthetic &amp; Recovery you will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with leading consultants and other like-minded professionals, who will respect and value what you bring to the multidisciplinary team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy opportunities to work on a varied caseload using technology, equipment and facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise, support and develop student and junior members of staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver high quality care and experience for our patients. A service which is always clinically effective, evidence based and appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As part of the wider hospital team you will interact with colleagues on the ward because you understand that continuity in patient care is key.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What are we looking for in a Theatre Practitioner / ODP – Anaesthetic &amp; Recovery? You will have;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualifications and experience relevant to your registration, including NMC or HCPC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post-registration experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and will be a great team worker. You will also be flexible and motivated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work in both disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What are the Benefits?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want you to be the best you can be. We promise that we will support you with training opportunities and career development options. For newly-qualified nurses we offer a one year preceptorship programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also offer a unique health and wellbeing focused benefits package. This includes free membership across all of our Fitness &amp; Wellbeing clubs, along with free private healthcare. Not only this but we also offer a range of lifestyle and financial wellbeing benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether you are currently in the NHS or a private setting, we are sure you will find your career with us motivating and rewarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like all of us at Nuffield Health, you do what you do because you care. Every one of our brilliant people is passionate about making a real difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary - £30k circa dependent on skills and experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cheltenham&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time, 37.5 hours  - Whilst the role is full-time 37.5 hours, we will accept part-time hours. Please contact us to discuss this further.&lt;/p&gt;
